literal "false"

\end_inset

, which were obtained via optimization of dissipation and dispersion relations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The geometric weight uses the form 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    \omega_f^G = \sqrt{S^{\frac{1}{d-1}}D_f^{-1}}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 is the number of spacial dimension, 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is the area of the interface, and 
\begin_inset Formula $D_f$
\end_inset

 is the distance between barycenters of the two cells. This form of geometric weight is also taken from 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
before ""
key "huang2022high"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The minimum problem 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    u_i^l = \mathop{\arg \min}(I)
\end{equation}
\end_inset

defines the solution to the variational reconstruction system. It is observed that 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 is a quadratic function of 
\begin_inset Formula $u_i^l, i = 1...N_{cell}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $I\geq 0$
\end_inset

, therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 is a positive semi-definite quadratic form about the global vector of reconstruction coefficients. Consequently, the minimum problem converts to a linear equation 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    \partialderivative{I}{u_i^l} = 0, l=1,2,\dots \mathrm{NDOF}(k),\ \ i=1,2,\dots N_{cell}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

This linear equation can be arranged in a cell-block form: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    \label{eq:vrBlockEq}
    \sum_{f=f_{ij},j\in S_i, j\neq i}{ \mathbf{A}_{ij} \us_i}
    =
    \sum_{f=f_{ij},j\in S_i, j\neq i}{ \mathbf{B}_{ij} \us_j + \mathbf{b}_{ij} (\overline{u}_j - \overline{u}_i)}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $S_i$
\end_inset

 is the compact stencil of 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 composed of cell 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 and its face neighbors. Local reconstruction coefficient vector is 
\begin_inset Formula $\us_i = [u_i^1,u_i^2\dots]\trans$
\end_inset

. The reconstruction coefficient matrices and vectors in 
