\end_inset

 times of matrix storage. But for inherently matrix-free flow solvers, such enlargement could require drastic modification and addition to the original codebase. The direct enlargement of the problem is referred to as the fully coupled approach in the current paper. Due to its complexity of implementation, the current research does not consider using fully coupled approach to solve DITR time stepping.
