LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:canonicalFF"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, as a result of nested 
\begin_inset Formula $\R$
\end_inset

 terms. Continuing with a general finite difference scheme will complicate the analysis, so we choose the first-order upwind difference as an example: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    \derivative{u_i}{t} = -a \frac{u_i - u_{i-1}}{\inc x}
    \label{eq:fdup1}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

Therefore from equations 
