\begin_inset Formula $\inc t = 0.00125$
\end_inset

. In the reference solution, restart information at 
\begin_inset Formula $t=200$
\end_inset

 is stored, in which the vortex street has fully developed. Next, starting from the 
\begin_inset Formula $t=200$
\end_inset

 flow field, combined with different time marching schemes and time step sizes varying from 
\begin_inset Formula $0.04$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $0.1$
\end_inset

, transient flow is simulated until 
\begin_inset Formula $t=210$
\end_inset

. CPU consumption and error values are evaluated. The transient errors are defined with 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    \begin{aligned}
        \|\epsilon_{My}\|_{t,2}^2
        = & \frac{1}{N_{t}}\sum_{i=1}^{N_t}{(M_{y,i}-M_{y,ref}(t_i))^2} \\
        \|\epsilon_{Mx}\|_{t,2}^2
        = & \frac{1}{N_{t}}\sum_{i=1}^{N_t}{(M_{x,i}-M_{x,ref}(t_i))^2}
    \end{aligned}
    \label{eq:vorstreetErr}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{t}$
\end_inset

 is the number of time steps for 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in(200,210]$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $t_i$
\end_inset

 is the time on time steps, and 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{y,i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{x,i}$
\end_inset

 are the norms of time derivatives of 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 momentum: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
    M_y = \int_{\Omega}{\left|\derivative{\rho u_y}{t}\right| \dd \Omega},\ \
    M_x = \int_{\Omega}{\left|\derivative{\rho u_x}{t}\right| \dd \Omega}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

Meanwhile, 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{y,ref}(t_i)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{x,ref}(t_i)$
\end_inset

 are those values obtained in the reference solution.
\end_layout

